    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i guess i struggle with it when the sentence is more complex. like, if i write \"the results were observed to be significant,\" how do i even change that without making it sound weird?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In complex sentences like that, you can use sentence rephrasing to convert the passive voice to active voice. For example, you could rephrase it to: \"Significant results were observed, which led to further investigation.\" or \"The results were significant, as observed, prompting further study.\" Alternatively, you could make more specific who or what is performing the observing, like \"Our team observed that the results were significant.\"",
      "source": "target",
